This game uses the advantage of having you win many games without losing at all, I had an 8 game win streak then after that the game had me hooked on it.... I started losing, every game, it would be impossible to win, no matter what. You can‚Äôt ever go in front of an opponents piece because he has a 90% chance of killing you. I did the math and 90% of the time I put a piece in front of the player he killed me. 
This game clearly lets you get hooked on it after winning much and satisfying yourself, however after you Start running low on gems (used to change the die) you start getting numbers you absolutely don‚Äôt need. And this strategy causes you to buy more gems in order for you to be able to change the die. After purchasing you‚Äôll suddenly win more games :) 
So after you run low in gems the game detects this, and it will parter you to people who have high gem numbers, thus having you lose to them. Until you get a high number of gems the game will have you with an opponent who has a lower number than you, and therefore that decides who wins the game. 
Because no matter how many useless numbers you get, and even how smart you use them, you don‚Äôt really need to be that intelligent in this game. It‚Äôs so simple that people don‚Äôt realise that the victory players get actually depends on what numbers they get on their die. Because of that, the better die you get, the most likely you will win. 
IT‚ÄôS A SCAM.

I don‚Äôt even know why I still play.
The game is supposed to be a strategy game with luck involved in it obviously. 
Somehow every player you play is the luckiest one. The die are simply not random. How is it possible that you roll as soon as an opponent is in front of you and you have a chance to eat them? Same thing goes for them, you can‚Äôt be in front of them regardless of the numerous spaces between you, because you will be eaten anyway! 
This game is just giving an advantage to people that don‚Äôt know how to play! 
What‚Äôs the whole point of having a strategy if the game is rigged or the phone plays by itself? I‚Äôve experienced first hand that someone rolled a double 3 times in a row and somehow that person still on the main board! 
It‚Äôs sad because it‚Äôs a good game to be played mostly because of quarantine time. 
The fact that you can use gems to re-throw takes away the reality of the game. 
To be fair, I only play for pure boredom since we can‚Äôt go outside. 
You can do better...

Absolutely love the Parcheesi game.  However, this game is supposed to be about strategy. Yea, sometimes, even in real life you get both lucky and unlucky and I understand that. In this game once cannot go in front of an opponent even if you are several spaces ahead because he/she will roll doubles and get within kill space from you. Also, the opponent 90% of the time gets a 5 to form the blockade on his Home space. I've had 2 of my tokens on goal several time and the opponent very close to home and somehow he wins the game? How is that even possible. Again, I know that will happen but not as frequently as it does in this app. When my token is ahead of theirs I can even guess what numbers they will roll. Some of my friends have stopped playing the game because of that same reason. Today I played my last game.

This game is fun , addictive & a great way to pass time but something to know is it is definitely rigged. You can tell because sometimes you will never get the right numbers to send your opponents home but they will ALWAYS get the right numbers to send you home . Sometimes in a game I will keep getting small numbers like a 2 and a 1 or a 3 and a 2 and my opponent will  high numbers like a 6 and a 5 or they will get doubles. The game picks who will win before the match even starts . Sometimes it is frustrating cause they will put you on a loosing streak and you will not win a game no matter how many times you play . You also need a 5 to come out and there have been times where they would not give me a 5 and all my pieces would be stuck at home while everyone else already had all of their pieces out . The game is fun but I see myself playing it less and less because of it being rigged. The game would be way more fun if it was random.

I just think that you have to use your intelligence to win the game, however the game is clearly messing with people. The dice numbers it throws are not ‚Äúrandom,‚Äù how is it possible that your opponent gets a number to kill you, and then you can kill them but you never get the number you wanted. Not only that but your opponent a lot of times does not even know how to play right and they still win because they get a lot of doubles. The game is just not fair, it can literally choose who will win, because it does not matter how much you know about the game, except the numbers the game gives you. Also, another thing, when I am playing with an opponent, they always get doubles two times and they do not get it the third time, but I do, the little amount of time I have got them. Also the game is dishonest, how is it that some people change their numbers, and they still do not get the number they wanted, or they get the same number. I mean if you are wasting your gems, then why bother, if you are getting the same number. My opponents always get doubles, but I do not. I just love the game a lot, but you got to do better. Some of my friends have already stop playing the game because of how unfair it is. Some people get really angry because the game is literally choosing who will win. The numbers are not random at all.

The game clearly was made to give people some type of booster that gives an advantage with the dice. The algorithms created for the throw of the dice are made to favor the other player. Simple mathematics makes it nearly imposible to be winning by a quite a few moves and then the opposing player getting just the right dice. I could happen, not saying it can‚Äôt, but the probabilities are like one in 36, then factor in that they need two more throws to get ahead then the probability becomes even harder to hit. It seems that I‚Äôve been on the receiving end of this various times around. Parch√≠s is a simple chance game, but you need to have a basic understanding of how die work and where to put your pieces in order to have a higher chance to win. This game clearly made it possible for lesser capable players to win by favoring them somehow. And even though you made a fair try to make it a good game you clearly didn‚Äôt have the right vision to make it into a profitable business. In other words, the creators are looking to make profit the wrong way. But hey, thats just my opinion, we‚Äôre all faced with the same problems.
